zsh cheatsheet
-------------
ctrl-t					- Search files/directories within current directory
ctrl-r					- Uses fzf (fuzzy search) to search history
bat					- Better version of cat (has / search)
glances					- Better version of htop (also in bash)
prettyping                            	- Better version of ping
preview					- Fuzzy search of current directory and preview files
ls *.rb | entr -r ruby main.rb		- When those Ruby files change, run main.rb
